B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
The FY 2027 increase reflects the shift from initial design to risk reduction testing and manufacturing plans development.
Title: Longshot                                                                                                                              -       52.660        151.500
Description: The LongShot program is developing and flight demonstrating an air-launched system capable of engaging multiple
adversary targets from standoff ranges using existing air-to-air missiles. LongShot will be deployed either externally from existing
fighters or internally from existing bombers. This system will capitalize on a slower speed, fuel-efficient air vehicle for ingress,
while retaining highly energetic air-to-air missiles for end-game target engagements, providing several key benefits that increase
weapon effectiveness. This program will address the stability and control challenges of launching air-to-air missiles from a
relatively small uninhabited system in an operational environment. Potential transition partners include the Navy and Air Force.

Prior to FY 2026, this program was funded in PE 0603286E, Project AIR-01.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Conduct weapon integration and ground testing.
- Complete fabrication and integration of flight test vehicles.
- Complete airworthiness certification and host aircraft integration.
- Conduct flight testing of the vehicle on a host aircraft.
- Conduct flight demonstrations validating vehicle release from a host aircraft.
- Conduct flight demonstrations validating air vehicle performance, stability and control through all phases of flight.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Continue flight demonstrations validating vehicle release from a host aircraft.
- Continue flight demonstrations validating vehicle performance, stability and control through all phases of flight.
- Conduct analysis and flight testing to expand flight envelope.
- Continue analysis and development of integrated mission systems to mature operationalized capabilities.
- Conduct alternate payload integration analysis based on Service-desired concepts of employment.
- Initiate alternate aircraft integration studies to include internal and external bomber weapons station integration and safe and
acceptable separation computational fluids dynamics analysis.
- Continue alternate launch options analysis and risk reduction testing to include palletized and ground launch options.
- Conduct propulsion integration studies to explore alternate engine options and engine operability analysis.
- Determine manufacturing approaches and design updates required for vehicle production at scale to inform Operational System
design and production planning.




