Title: Process Intensified Energetics (PIE)                                                                                                  -              -       13.047
Description: The Process Intensified Energetics (PIE) program will develop the tools and processing methods to safely turn
locally available materials into reliable energetics in order to enable the production of fieldable warheads and rocket motors. This
program will develop a flexible, robust, and agile manufacturing platform for the production of energetics from locally available
material (industrial chemicals to crude oil), leveraging innovative chemical processing and manufacturing controls to dramatically
drive down the timeframes and scale needed for production from days to hours and from full-scale factories to containers. PIE will
work with diverse input materials and conversion methodologies to continually increase rate, diversity, and quality of energetic
output, demonstrating both explosive and propellant manufacturing from a set of locally sourced materials, verified by small-scale
propellant and explosive testing. Technology developed under this program will be transitioned to the Services. Applied research
related to this effort is funded in PE 0602025E, Project MSL-01.

FY 2027 Plans:
- Execute end-to-end validation testing on novel energetic materials developed from diverse materials.
- Conduct a system readiness review based on outcomes from sub-scale demonstrations and validation tests on modular
platforms.
- Demonstrate pilot scale production capability on modular platforms.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:




