Title: Advanced Complex Systems Studies and Concepts                                                                                           -        0.101         62.348
Description: Studies conducted under this program will examine and evaluate emerging technologies and system concepts
for applicability to military use. This includes the degree and scope of potential impact and improvements to military operations,
mission utility, and warfighter capability. Studies are also conducted to analyze emerging aerospace threats along with possible
methods and technologies for countermeasures. The feasibility of achieving potential improvements, in terms of resources,
schedule, and technological risk, is also evaluated. The results from these studies are used, in part, to formulate future prototype
development programs or refocus ongoing work. Topics include: methods of defeating enemy anti-aircraft attacks; munition
technologies to increase precision, range, endurance, and lethality of weapons for a variety of mission sets; novel launch systems;
air vehicle control, power, propulsion, materials, and architectures; payload and cargo handling systems; applying artificial
intelligence to low earth orbit (LEO) constellation operations to enable collaboration between space, air, maritime, and ground
platforms in anti-access/area denial (A2/AD) theaters; robust architectures for precision navigation and timing; enabling operations
in Cislunar space; novel approaches to space domain awareness; integration of commercial capabilities into military operations;
and on-orbit software environments.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Explore and refine advanced platform concepts to deliver integrated, cross-domain dominance solutions at disruptive scale and
unprecedented penetration capabilities.
- Evaluate innovative architectures, operational concepts, and propulsion technologies spanning chemical rocket, airbreathing,
and hybrid air vehicle systems to effectively counter and penetrate advanced Anti-Access/Area Denial (A2/AD) environments.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Initiate research approaches for technologies that enable decisive military effects at distances from the tactical to the strategic.
- Explore new insertion routes and cost/fuel efficient range improvements.
- Research technologies for pervasive persistence for observation and constant low-level engagement, supporting blue force and
allies.
- Evaluate life extension and upgrading existing systems with new technologies to confound adversary advances.
- Explore novel engineering, technology, and systems approaches that have the potential to change the traditional calculus for
military advantage.
- Investigate low-cost mass/volume in quantity to overwhelm defense and deliver effects.
- Explore decoy denial of service attack and new sensing modalities that change the game for defense operations.
- Research capabilities to create doubt among adversaries and strengthen resolve of allies.


