A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Automated Test and ReTest (ATRT) Enterprise Rapid Capability develops, integrates, and deploys novel capabilities aggregated from mature technologies in support
of Distributed Maritime Operations. ATRT technologies provide essential development, assessment, and operational analysis capabilities to streamline testing and
certification for both single systems and systems of systems capabilities in order to reduce development time for new capabilities from years to weeks. Further, ATRT
leverages support to refactoring, development, and assessment of Artificial Intelligence / Machine Learning (AI/ML) aids with other applications to deliver warfighting
capability. The integration of legacy code and systems across the Naval warfighting portfolio aims to achieve an open integration and interoperability environment.
These capabilities are enabled through the use of virtualized systems of systems, automated test and analysis, automated certification, rapid interface development, and
field with data collection and edge analytics. These technologies are at the heart of the Navy's rapid capability approach, which combines digital engineering tools with
evolutionary approaches to requirements generation, operational testing, and deployment.

Project funding supports application of Automated Test and Analysis (ATA) technologies to software-intensive acquisition programs through continued development and
commercialization of ATRT Small Business Innovation Research (SBIR) technologies across the Navy enterprise. These SBIR derived technologies enable the Navy
enterprise to make rapid capability improvements through software updates while maintaining a continuous Authority to Operate (ATO) on a common digital warfighting
platform, and in enterprise sandbox technologies.

