FY 2026 Plans:
Focus on continuation of planning efforts and begin initial execution for testing in FY 2026-2030:
- Utilizing DT Events on LPD 29 to reduce risks for FOT&E Surface Warfare (SUW) testing planned for FY 2028.
- Cybersecurity Test Planning and conducting the manpower and equipment intensive Cyber Cooperative
Vulnerability
Identification (CVI) and Adversarial Cyber DT&E (ACD) for additional LPD Network Enclaves.
- Interoperability Test Planning (Net Ready-Key Performance Parameter).
- Continue LFT&E modeling and simulation support for Shock Trial Alternative to assess Flight II ship shock
hardness and inform corrective design modifications.
- Continue DT&E and FOT&E efforts for the EASR/Ship Self Defense, including the Plans, Exercises, Targets,
and Missiles to demonstrate Flight II combat system capability.
- Overall test support, documentation/plans (TEMP), coordination, and event conduct support.
Efforts will also focus on implementation of new GFE/CFE on new construction LPDs:

                                                                                                                           Integration

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                        FY 2027     FY 2027       FY 2027
                                                                                                                 FY 2025   FY 2026      Base        OOC           Total
- Continuation of assessment of HERO/HERP for ship, aircraft, and weapons integration with EASR, SPY-6(V)2
and other associated radar-to-ship integration activities for the new radar.
- Cybersecurity risk assessments, validation, and approvals under RMF process for new, modified, or continued
fielding of LPD unique systems.
- Qualification of systems/equipment impacted by obsolescence such as shock, vibration, and EMI for new
systems.
- Study of obsolescence cases and resolution of emergent items identified under Diminishing Manufacturing
Sources and Material Shortages (DMSMS)/Obsolescence working groups.
- Study and assessments of ship impacts due to GFE system obsolescence and technology refresh, including
Configuration Management and Concurrent Engineering activities.
- Continue Software Support Activity/ Development & Integration for management and evaluation of new/unique
LPD
HM&E systems, networks, and control systems.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
- Continue DT&E and FOT&E efforts for the Enterprise Air Search Radar (EASR)/Ship Self Defense, including
the Plans, Exercises, Targets, and Missiles to demonstrate Flight II combat system capability.
- Cybersecurity Test Planning and conducting the manpower and equipment intensive Cyber Cooperative
Vulnerability Identification (CVI) and Adversarial Cyber DT&E (ACD) for additional LPD Network Enclaves.
- Interoperability Test Planning (Net Ready-Key Performance Parameter).
- Commence planning efforts for a Shock Trial event which will either be a Modeling and Simulation (M&S) of a
Shock Trial or a Full Ship Shock Trials (FSST).
- Overall test support, documentation/plans (TEMP), coordination, and event conduct support.
Efforts will also focus on implementation of new GFE/CFE on new construction LPDs:
- Cybersecurity risk assessments, validation, and approvals under RMF process for new, modified, or continued
fielding of LPD unique systems.
- Qualification of systems/equipment such as shock, vibration, and Electromagnetic Interference (EMI) for new
systems.
- Qualification and validation of various system software.
- Study and resolution of emergent items identified under Diminishing Manufacturing Sources and Material
Shortages (DMSMS) working groups.
- Study and assess ship impact due to aging GFE systems and technology refresh, including Configuration
Management and Concurrent Engineering activities.

                                                                                                                              Integration

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                           FY 2027     FY 2027       FY 2027
                                                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026      Base        OOC           Total
- Provide detail design engineering efforts to include the non-recurring class design change paper development.
- Continue Software Support Activity/ Development & Integration for management and evaluation of new/unique
LPD HM&E systems, networks, and control systems.
- Investigate, test, and develop a solution to existing electrical design issues associated with common mode
voltage in the High Efficiency Super Capacity (HESC) variable speed drive (VSD) cabinet and EMI Filter.
FY 2027 OOC Plans:
N/A
