D. Acquisition Strategy
Firestarter conducts late-stage Science and Technology (S&T) for tech demo and tech transition to warfighter employment. All contracts within this project are awarded
using full and open competition and utilize evolutionary capability and incremental development. Where appropriate, collaborative efforts are conducted with services
and agencies within the Department of the Air Force to result in more robust and cost-effective solutions. Contracting activities are primarily done through other agencies
when deemed more advantageous. All aspects of the Firestarter project are managed by the AF Research Laboratory (AFRL).



