A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Small Diameter Bomb Increment II (SDB II) is an ACAT 1C joint Department of the Air Force (USAF) and Department of the Navy (DON) program, with the USAF as
the lead service. The SDB II increases joint lethality in contested environments. The SDB II can strike a diverse set of targets inside an adversary's air and missile
defense networks to destroy mobile platforms through the weather. With increased loadout, range, and munitions effect the network enabled SDB II enhances close
combat lethality in complex terrain and provides a net-centric operations capability. BRU-61C/A is a modification of the USAF BRU-61B/A upgraded for DON and F-35
environmental requirements. The BRU-61C/A is Universal Armament Interface (UAI) capable, pneumatic rack capable of carrying four SDB II's at once. The threshold
aircraft for the USAF is the F-15E, and for the DON is F-35B and F-35C. F/A-18 E/F is an objective platform for the DON.

The DON has adjusted the platform integration strategy through the inclusion of F/A-18 E/F using BRU-55 to deliver the capability to the warfighter aligned to the
adjusted F-35 program's schedule.

BUDGET ACTIVITY JUSTIFICATION: This program is funded under SYSTEM DEVELOPMENT AND DEMONSTRATION because it includes those projects that have
passed Milestone B approval and are conducting engineering and manufacturing development tasks aimed at meeting validated requirement prior to full-rate production
decision.

