       The FY 2027 ($0.263M) decrease is due to reduced testing of small-scale proof of concepts of future Expeditionary Carry-On Networks capabilities in support of
       naval exercises and the Expeditionary Mine Countermeasure (ExMCM) companies.

       Schedule:

       (2126) Link 16: Mod A(v)6 Integration Testing was completed in FY26Q1 vice FY25Q4 as planned due to a delay in receiving the MOS Mod integration kits from
       the vendor. The A(v)6 DT/AOC event title was updated to A(v)6 DT to reflect the OPTEVFOR AOC no longer being required and event completion was updated
       from FY25Q4 to FY26Q2 to align with the next ship installation opportunity. MOS MIDS JTRS A(v)6 FDR and MOS MOD A(v)6 FDR events were removed from
       the schedule to reflect the formal fielding decision review event to no longer be a requirement.

       (2126) C2P Changes: Adaptive Tactical Data Link System (ATS) Assessment was added to the schedule starting in FY25Q2 and C2P Mod IOC was added to the
       schedule in FY27Q2 as the milestones were missing. C2P Modernization Development, Integration and Systems Engineering and Minor Engineering Updates
       have been included in FY31 as the fiscal year is now reflected in the reporting period. Due to budget constraints, C2P Mod Pre-Planned Product Improvement
       (P3I) capability development efforts have been discontinued in FY26Q4 prior to its planned completion as the Program transitions to only minor engineering
       updates starting in FY27 and P3I Capability Drop (CD) 26 was removed from the schedule. C2P Mod SW Release C IV&V commencement has been deferred
       from FY25Q3 to FY25Q4 due to resource constraints from other testing activities. As a result, Mod Combat System Integration/Link 22 Certification start was
       shifted back one quarter to FY26Q3; Minor Engineering Updates shifted from FY27Q1 to FY27Q2; and Mod/Link 22 FDR/IOC was reprogrammed from FY28Q2
       to FY28Q4.

       (2126) LMMT Changes: Capability Drop (CD) 4 events were removed as a Fleet has not defined Tactical Targeting Networking Technology (TTNT) Monitoring
       and Management requirements prior to LMMT incorporation. This impacted the following events: CD4 development Study, CD4 IV&V, CD4 Production Release,
       CD4 DT, CD4 FTR, CD4 ACT, and CD4 FDR. Events associated with the Maintenance Release (MR) of LMMT CD3, which includes Link 16 Concurrent Multi-
       Netting (CMN-4) and ECPs to improve LMMT's functionality, were missing from the prior schedule and therefore added. This includes CD3 MR Development
       Study, which concluded in FY25Q4; CD3 MR IV&V that commenced in FY26Q1; and CD3 MR Production Release anticipated in FY27Q1.

